Explain the setTimeout() and setInterval() functions in JavaScript. How are they 
used for timing events? 


1. setTimeout()
Purpose: Runs a function once after a specified delay (in milliseconds).

Syntax:

setTimeout(function, delayInMilliseconds);
How it works: Schedules a one-time execution of the function after the delay.

Example:

setTimeout(() => {
  console.log("This runs after 2 seconds");
}, 2000);

2. setInterval()
Purpose: Runs a function repeatedly at specified intervals (in milliseconds).

Syntax:

setInterval(function, intervalInMilliseconds);
How it works: Calls the function repeatedly every interval until stopped.

Example:

setInterval(() => {
  console.log("This runs every 3 seconds");
}, 3000);


